{"title_page": "Communist Youth Movement (Netherlands)", "text_new": "{{Infobox political youth organization\n|name = Communist Youth Movement\n|native_name = Communistische Jongeren Beweging\n|colorcode = red\n|logo = [[File:Cjblogo 2010 wiki en-01.png|CJB Logo]]\n|founded = 21 September 2003\n|headquarters = Haarlemmerweg 177, 1051 LB, [[Amsterdam]]\n|ideology = [[Marxism-Leninism]]\n|mother party = [[New Communist Party of the Netherlands]]\n|international = [[World Federation of Democratic Youth]] (pending member)\n|regional1_type =\n|regional1_name = \n|website = [http://www.voorwaarts.net/ voorwaarts.net]\n}}\n'''Communist Youth Movement''' (in [[Dutch language|Dutch]]: ''Communistische Jongeren Beweging'') is a political youth organisation in the [[Netherlands]]. The CJB was founded on 21 September 2003, as an independent continuation of the youth of the [[New Communist Party of the Netherlands]], ''NCPN Jongeren'' (NCPN Youth). It is the official youth organisation of the NCPN, and it publishes ''Voorwaarts!'' (Onwards!), an online magazine. \n\n== Organization ==\nThe CJB in organized in different regions and chapters. The highest membership body is the general meeting, which is held once every two years. The movement is organized along the lines of [[democratic centralism]]. Chapters are active in [[North Holland]], [[Overijssel]], [[West Brabant]], [[South Holland|Zuid Holland]] and [[Groningen (province)|Groningen.]] There are also members throughout the country who are not part of a chapter. \n\nThe CJB is an autonomous youth organisation, but is aligned with the NCPN politically. The CJB permits only dual membership of the NCPN and not of other [[List of political parties in the Netherlands|political parties]]. Exceptions are possible, such as CJB members  who are abroad joining their local communist organization, or members with an [[Demography of the Netherlands|immigrant]] background joining a communist party wich is active in their [[diaspora]] (for instance [[Communist Party of Chile|Chile]], [[Communist Party of Greece|Greece]] or [[Iraqi Communist Party|Iraq]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voorwaarts.net/statuten/|title=Statuten - Communistische Jongeren Beweging|website=Voorwaarts.net|language=nl-NL|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>. \n\n== Political Activities ==\n[[File:Cjb tradeunion.jpg|left|thumb|CJB members at a trade union action]]The main goal of the CJB is raising class consciousness and emancipation of young people from the workers and unemployed class in the Netherlands<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voorwaarts.net/wat-is-de-cjb/|title=Over de CJB - Communistische Jongerenbeweging van Nederland|website=Voorwaarts.net|language=nl-NL|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>. It's members are active in [[Anti-fascism|anti-fascist]] movements, the student movement and as [[Union organizer|organizers]] in the [[Federatie Nederlandse Vakbeweging|labor movement.]] \n\nThe CJB participates in the yearly [[International Workers' Day|Labor Day]] demonstrations organized by the [[Federatie Nederlandse Vakbeweging|FNV]] and the the demonstration on the [[International Day for the Elimination of Racial Discrimination]]. In it's anti-fascist work the CJB cooperates with the ''AFVN/Bond van Antifascisten''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.omroepbrabant.nl/nieuws/3040719/Protest-tegen-nazi-kunst-in-Design-Museum-Den-Bosch-Geen-nazi-propaganda-in-museum|title=Protest tegen nazi-kunst in Design Museum Den Bosch: 'Geen nazi-propaganda in museum'|website=Omroep Brabant|language=NL|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\nThe movement also organizes an alternative remembrance of the [[February strike|February Strike]]. In contrast to the official remembrance, the remembrance of the CJB specifically celebrates the communist ideology of the strikers<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voorwaarts.net/viering-februaristaking-2020-antifascisme-geef-je-door/|title=Viering Februaristaking 2020: Antifascisme Geef Je Door!|last=Feb 13|first=|last2=CJB|first2=|date=2020-02-13|website=Voorwaarts.net|language=nl-NL|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-22|last3=|last4=|last5=|last6=|last7=}}</ref>.<br />\n\n== International ==\nThe CJB participates in the Meeting of European Communist Youth Organizations (MECYO) and is a pending member of the [[World Federation of Democratic Youth]] (WFDY). It enjoys good bilateral relations with the [[Socialist German Workers Youth|SDAJ]] and the [[Comac (youth movement)|COMAC]]. The movement regularly organizes actions in solidarity with [[Cuba]], [[Venezuela]] and [[Bolivia]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voorwaarts.net/succesvolle-politieke-bijeenkomst-imperialisme-of-socialisme-70-jaar-navo-100-jaar-komintern/|title=Succesvolle politieke bijeenkomst: \u2018Imperialisme of Socialisme? 70 jaar NAVO - 100 jaar Komintern'|last=Dec 17|first=|last2=|first2=|date=2019-12-17|website=Voorwaarts.net|language=nl|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-22|last3=|last4=|first4=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voorwaarts.net/verklaring-ncpn-en-cjb-over-de-staatsgreep-in-bolivia/|title=Verklaring NCPN en CJB over de staatsgreep in Bolivia|last=Nov 15|first=|last2=|first2=|date=2019-11-15|website=Voorwaarts.net|language=nl-NL|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-22|last3=|last4=|last5=|last6=|first6=|last7=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voorwaarts.net/verklaring-over-de-couppoging-in-venezuela/|title=Verklaring over de couppoging in Venezuela|last=Jan 24|first=|last2=|first2=|date=2019-01-24|website=Voorwaarts.net|language=nl-NL|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-22|last3=|last4=|first4=}}</ref>. \n\n==See also==\n* [[General Dutch Youth League|Algemeen Nederlands Jeugd Verbond]] ( the youth organization of the [[Communist Party of the Netherlands|CPN]] and a predecessor of the CJB)\n*[[New Communist Party of the Netherlands]]\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100726035312/http://www.voorwaarts.net/cjblog/international-english/ English CJB website]\n* [http://www.voorwaarts.net/ ''Voorwaarts!'', webmagazine of the CJB]\n*[https://www.groene.nl/artikel/communisme-als-levenshouding De terugkeer van Marx: Het profiel van de NCPN Communisme als levenshouding] (in [[Dutch language|Dutch]]). A profile in [[De Groene Amsterdammer]] of the CJB and NCPN\n\n{{Dutch political youth organizations}}\n\n== References ==\n[[Category:Youth wings of communist parties]]\n[[Category:Youth wings of political parties in the Netherlands]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox political youth organization\n|name = Communist Youth Movement\n|native_name = Communistische Jongeren Beweging\n|colorcode = red\n|logo = [[File:Cjblogo 2010 wiki en-01.png|CJB Logo]]\n|founded = 21 September 2003\n|headquarters = Haarlemmerweg 177, 1051 LB, [[Amsterdam]]\n|ideology = [[Marxism-Leninism]]\n|mother party = [[New Communist Party of the Netherlands]]\n|international = [[World Federation of Democratic Youth]] (pending member)\n|regional1_type =\n|regional1_name = \n|website = [http://www.voorwaarts.net/ voorwaarts.net]\n}}\n'''Communist Youth Movement''' (in [[Dutch language|Dutch]]: ''Communistische Jongeren Beweging'') is a political youth organisation in the [[Netherlands]]. The CJB was founded on 21 September 2003, as an independent continuation of the youth of the [[New Communist Party of the Netherlands]], ''NCPN Jongeren'' (NCPN Youth). It is the official youth organisation of the NCPN, and it publishes ''Voorwaarts!'' (Onwards!), an online magazine. \n\n== Organization ==\nThe CJB in organized in different regions and chapters. The highest membership body is the general meeting, which is held once every two years. The movement is organized along the lines of [[democratic centralism]]. Chapters are active in [[North Holland]], [[Overijssel]], [[West Brabant]], [[South Holland|Zuid Holland]] and [[Groningen (province)|Groningen.]] There are also members