{"title_page": "Pauline Turner", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=April 2020}}\n{{Short description|Scottish actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Pauline Turner\n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   =\n| birth_place  = [[Dumbarton]], [[Scotland]]\n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = 1994\u2013present\n| spouse       = \n| children     = \n| alma mater   =\n| television   = ''[[Martin Chuzzlewit (TV series)| Martin Chuzzlewit]]'' <br> ''[[Peaky Blinders (TV series)|Peaky Blinders]]'' <br>\n}}\n\n'''Pauline Turner''' is a Scottish actress, known for her role as Mary Graham on the [[BBC One|BBC]] drama series ''[[Martin Chuzzlewit (TV series)| Martin Chuzzlewit]]''<ref>{{cite news |title=Martin Chuzzlewit, 19 March 1995 |url=https://variety.com/1995/film/reviews/martin-chuzzlewit-1200441019/ |accessdate=21 April 2020 |publisher=Variety}}</ref>(1994), as Frances on the [[BBC One|BBC]] period drama series ''[[Peaky Blinders (TV series)|Peaky Blinders]]'' (2017-2019) and as June Begbie on the film ''[[T2 Trainspotting]]''<ref>{{cite news |title=Dumbarton actress has starring role in Trainspotting 2, 1 February 2017 |url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/local-news/dumbarton-actress-starring-role-trainspotting-9737295 |accessdate=21 April 2020 |publisher=Daily Record}}</ref> (2017).\n\n==Early Life==\nBell was born and raised in [[Dumbarton]], [[West Dunbartonshire]]. She attended Knoxland Primary school and finished her secondary education at [[Dumbarton Academy]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Goodnight Mister Tom (film)|Goodnight Mister Tom]]''\n| Annie Hartridge\n| \n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Young Adam (film)|Young Adam]]''\n| Connie\n| \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[T2 Trainspotting]]''\n| June\n| \n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Beyond Existance''\n| Waitress\n| ''post-production''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable